    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prints made using a process of relief printing, in which the nonprinting areas of the block or plate are carved, engraved, or etched away, leaving the original plane surface raised so that ink is deposited and transferred to paper.</Note_Text>
